'''Angela Ann Knight''' (born [[31 October]], [[1950]]) is a [[British]] [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] politician.  She was [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for [[Erewash (UK Parliament constituency)|Erewash]] from 1992 to 1997, when she lost the seat to [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour's]] [[Liz Blackman]].  She was [[Economic Secretary to the Treasury]] from 1995 to 1997.

